ul.li: (Lowercase): Uses SHR (Shift Right) to break reversible linearity.
(Uppercase): Uses ROTR (Rotate) only for maximal diffusion without bit loss.

g.text: - Ops: 2x ROTR, 1x SHR - Type: Non-reversible (SHR destroys 3 MSB) - Purpose: Diffusion in message schedule expansion
- Ops: 2x ROTR, 1x SHR - Type: Non-reversible (SHR destroys 10 MSB) - Purpose: Recurrence for W[16..63]
- Ops: 3x ROTR (Pure rotation) - Type: Reversible bit diffusion - Usage: Applied to register 'a' (Working Variable)
- Ops: 3x ROTR (Pure rotation) - Type: Reversible bit diffusion - Usage: Applied to register 'e' (Working Variable)
